🧠 1. getOwner() / setOwner(Identity owner):-
👉 Concept:
Owner = final responsible person (decision maker)(current assignee)
🔹 setOwner(Identity owner):-
Ye user hi normally approve/reject karega
Identity manager = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "manager");
item.setOwner(manager);

🧠 2. getAssignee() / setAssignee(Identity identity):-
👉 Concept:-
Assignee = jo currently task handle kar raha hai
🔹 setAssignee(Identity identity):-
WorkItem ko kisi user ko assign karta hai
Ye change ho sakta hai (delegation / reassignment)
Identity lead = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "teamlead");
item.setAssignee(lead);

🧠 3. getTarget() / setTarget(String target):-
👉 Concept:-
Target = jis object pe work ho raha hai (context of work)
🔹 setTarget(String target):-
WorkItem kis cheez ke liye bana hai wo define karta hai
item.setTarget("Identity:john.doe");
🔥 Real Examples of Target:-
User ID
Account ID
Role Name
Request ID
Application Name
