🧠 1. setOwner(String owner) (WorkItemConfig):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Ye default owner define karta hai WorkItem ke liye
Matlab: jab WorkItem create hoga → ye config decide karega kisko assign karna hai.
🔹 Example:-
WorkItemConfig config = new WorkItemConfig();
config.setOwner("manager");

👉 Iska matlab:-
Har WorkItem ka owner = "manager" hoga (default).

🔥 Real Flow (Most Important):-
Workflow start
   ↓
WorkItemConfig check
   ↓
Owner (String) resolve hota hai
   ↓
Identity object fetch hota hai
   ↓
WorkItem.setOwner(Identity)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 Step-by-Step Real Flow (Under the Hood):-
🔷 Step 1: WorkItemConfig
config.setOwner("manager");
👉 Yaha sirf string "manager" store hota hai
👉 Ye ek instruction hai, actual user nahi

🔷 Step 2: Workflow / Engine start
👉 Jab workflow run hota hai:
System padhta hai → owner = "manager"

🔷 Step 3: Identity Resolve hota hai
Identity manager = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "manager");
👉 System database se actual user object nikalta hai

🔷 Step 4: WorkItem create hota hai
WorkItem item = new WorkItem();
item.setOwner(manager);
👉 Ab:
String → convert ho gaya real Identity object me

🔷 Step 5: UI me show hota hai
👉 Manager login karega → usko WorkItem dikhega.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🧠 1. setOwnerRule(String rule):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
Ye dynamic owner assign karne ke liye rule set karta hai
Static "manager" dene ki jagah → logic se decide hota hai kaun owner hoga
🔹 Example:-
config.setOwnerRule("managerRule");

👉 Matlab:-
System bolega → “owner directly fix mat karo”
“Rule run karo aur decide karo kaun owner hoga”

✅ Real Working Owner Rule (Manager Based)
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.tools.GeneralException;

public Identity managerOwnerRule(SailPointContext context, Identity identity) throws GeneralException {

    // Check if identity null hai
    if (identity == null) {
        return null;
    }

    // Manager nikalna
    Identity manager = identity.getManager();

    // Agar manager exist karta hai
    if (manager != null) {
        return manager;
    }

    // Fallback: Agar manager nahi hai to admin assign karo
    Identity admin = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "spadmin");

    return admin;
}
