👉 Kya karta hai?
Ye dynamic escalation define karta hai
Matlab: fixed "admin" dene ki jagah → rule decide karega kisko escalate karna hai.

🧠 2. getEscalationRule()
👉 Kya karta hai?
Jo rule name set hai wo return karta hai
String rule = config.getEscalationRule();
System.out.println(rule); // escalationRule

✅ Multi-Level Escalation Rule (Working Code):-
import sailpoint.object.Identity;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.tools.GeneralException;

public Identity escalationRule(SailPointContext context, Identity currentOwner) throws GeneralException {

    // 1️⃣ Agar current owner null hai → admin
    if (currentOwner == null) {
        return context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "spadmin");
    }

    // 2️⃣ Current owner ka manager
    Identity manager = currentOwner.getManager();
    if (manager != null) {
        return manager;
    }

    // 3️⃣ Manager ka manager (2nd level escalation)
    if (manager != null && manager.getManager() != null) {
        return manager.getManager();
    }

    // 4️⃣ Final fallback → admin
    return context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "spadmin");
}
